object.script:
currentGear = 0 lastUp = false lastNeutral = false lastUp = false
-- Tick function that will be executed every logic tick function onTick() currentUp = input.getBool(1) currentNeutral = input.getBool(2) currentDown = input.getBool(3)
if(not lastUp and currentUp and currentGear < 4) then currentGear = currentGear + 1 elseif(not lastDown and currentDown and currentGear > 0) then currentGear = currentGear - 1 elseif(not lastNeutral and currentNeutral) then currentGear = 0 end
output.setNumber(1, currentGear)
lastUp = currentUp lastNeutral = currentNeutral lastDown = currentDown end
-- Draw function that will be executed when this script renders to a screen function onDraw() w = screen.getWidth() -- Get the screen's width and height h = screen.getHeight() screen.setColor(0, 0, 0) -- Set draw color to green
screen.drawTextBox(1, 1, w, h, string.format("Current Gear: "), h_align, v_align) end

object.script:
waypoints = {} counter = 0 currentC = 0 lastPulse = false
function onTick() reset = input.getBool(3) pulse = input.getBool(4)
w = input.getNumber(1) h = input.getNumber(2)
zoom = input.getNumber(7) output.setNumber(1, zoom) x = input.getNumber(8) y = input.getNumber(9) bearing = input.getNumber(10) newX = input.getNumber(11) newY = input.getNumber(12) currentC = input.getNumber(13)
if (reset) then waypoints = {} counter = 0 end
if (pulse and not lastPulse) then
waypoints[counter * 2 + 1] = newX waypoints[counter * 2 + 2] = newY
counter = counter + 1 end
lastPulse = pulse end
function onDraw()
w = screen.getWidth() h = screen.getHeight()
if (w<h) then size = w * 0.04 else size = h * 0.04 end
screen.drawMap(x, y, zoom)
firstX, firstY = map.mapToScreen(x, y, zoom, w, h, x, y)
for i = currentC, counter - 1 do secondX, secondY = map.mapToScreen(x, y, zoom, w, h, waypoints[i * 2 + 1], waypoints[i * 2 + 2]) radius = cramp(0, 1, (1 - zoom / 10)) * size
screen.setColor(255, 165, 0, 255) screen.drawLine(firstX, firstY, secondX, secondY)
screen.setColor(0, 0, 0, 240) screen.drawCircleF(secondX, secondY, radius)
screen.setColor(0, 0, 0, 255) screen.drawText(secondX + radius, secondY + radius, string.format("%.0f", i))
firstX = secondX firstY = secondY end
screen.setColor(200, 0, 0, 128) drawCurrentPosition(w, h)
screen.setColor(220, 0, 0, 255) screen.drawRectF(findRectCenterX(w, 2), findRectCenterY(h, 2), 2, 2) end
function drawCurrentPosition(w, h) if (w<h) then radius = w * 0.09 else radius = h * 0.09 end cx = w/2 cy = h/2 compassDegrees = bearing * -360 % 360 translatedBearing = compassDegrees + 90 rad1 = math.rad(translatedBearing) rad2 = math.rad(translatedBearing + 140) rad3 = math.rad(translatedBearing + 220) x1 = cx - radius * math.cos(rad1) y1 = cy - radius * math.sin(rad1) x2 = cx - radius * math.cos(rad2) y2 = cy - radius * math.sin(rad2) x3 = cx - radius * math.cos(rad3) y3 = cy - radius * math.sin(rad3) screen.drawTriangleF(x1, y1, x2, y2, x3, y3) end
function findRectCenterX(w, rectW) return w/2 - (rectW / 2) end
function findRectCenterY(h, rectH) return h/2 - (rectH / 2) end
function cramp(min, max, value) if (value < min) then return min elseif (value > max) then return max else return value end end

safezone = 10
waypoints = {} counter = 0 currentC = 0
onRoute = false
lastPulse = false
function onTick() start = input.getBool(2) reset = input.getBool(3) pulse = input.getBool(4)
currentX = input.getNumber(4) currentY = input.getNumber(5) compass = input.getNumber(6) bearing = compass * -360 % 360
if (pulse and not lastPulse) then x = input.getNumber(2) y = input.getNumber(3)
output.setNumber(1, x) output.setNumber(2, y)
waypoints[counter * 2 + 1] = x waypoints[counter * 2 + 2] = y counter = counter + 1 end
if (start and counter > 0) then onRoute = true end
if (reset) then waypoints = {} counter = 0 currentC = 0 onRoute = false end
if (onRoute and currentC ~= counter) then angle = math.atan(waypoints[currentC * 2 + 2] - currentY, waypoints[currentC * 2 + 1] - currentX) * (180 / math.pi) - 90
--adjust the angle calculation if (angle < 0) then angle = angle * -1 elseif (angle > 0) then angle = angle + 270 end
--determine to which side to turn right = angle - bearing if (right < 0) then right = right + 360 end left = 360 - right
--turn rudders if (left < right) then if (left < safezone) then rudders = -left / safezone else rudders = -1 end elseif (left > right) then if (right < safezone) then rudders = right / safezone else rudders = 1 end else rudders = 0 end
--determine when the checkpoint is reached distance = calculateDistance(waypoints[currentC * 2 + 1], currentX, waypoints[currentC * 2 + 2],currentY) if (distance < 10) then currentC = currentC + 1 end elseif (onRoute and currentC == counter) then waypoints = {} counter = 0 currentC = 0 onRoute = false end
totalDistance = 0 firstX, firstY = currentX, currentY
for i = currentC, counter - 1 do secondX, secondY = waypoints[currentC * 2 + 1], waypoints[currentC * 2 + 2] totalDistance = totalDistance + calculateDistance(firstX, secondX, firstY, secondY) end
output.setBool(1, onRoute) output.setBool(2, reset) output.setBool(3, pulse)
output.setNumber(3, rudders) output.setNumber(4, counter) output.setNumber(5, currentC) output.setNumber(6, totalDistance)
lastPulse = pulse end
function calculateDistance(x1, y1, x2, y2) return math.sqrt((x1 - x2)^2 + (y1 - y2)^2) end

object.script:
speed = property.getNumber("Speed")
Rup = false Gup = false Bup = false
R = 255 G = 170 B = 85
function onTick() if (R >= 255) then Rup = false elseif (R <= 0) then Rup = true
if (G >= 255) then Gup = false elseif (G <= 0) then Gup = true
if (B >= 255) then Bup = false elseif (B <= 0) then Bup = true
if (Rup) then R = R + speed else R = R - speed end
if (Bup) then B = B + speed else B = B - speed end
if (Gup) then G = G + speed else G = G - speed end
output.setNumber(1, R) output.setNumber(2, G) output.setNumber(3, B) end
